        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>Preconditions:</p>

<p><b>System Preconditions:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Urban Grocers API service is running and accessible</li>
	<li>Base URL is configured and reachable</li>
	<li>API endpoint <tt>/api/v1/kits/:id/products</tt> is available</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Test Environment Preconditions:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Postman is installed and configured</li>
	<li>Valid base URL is available for testing</li>
	<li>Network connectivity to the API service</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Data Preconditions:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Valid kit ID exists in the system (e.g., id=6)</li>
	<li>Valid product ID exists (e.g., id=5)</li>
	<li>Test quantity value = 0 (for boundary testing)</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Expected System Behavior:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>API should validate quantity values</li>
	<li>System should reject quantity = 0 as invalid</li>
	<li>API should return 400 Bad Request for zero quantity</li>
</ul>


<p>Steps for reproducer:</p>

<p>1.Open Postman<br/>
2.Set request type to POST<br/>
3.Enter URL: <span class="error">&#91;base_url&#93;</span>/api/v1/kits/:id/products<br/>
4.Set kit ID in path parameter (like id=6)<br/>
5.Send request with valid product ID but quantity = 0<br/>
6.Verify the system rejects zero quantity (you can't add 0 of a product to a kit)<br/>
7.User gets Status: 400 Bad Request</p>

<p>Request body:</p>

<p>{<br/>
  "productsList": [</p>
    {
      "id": 5,
      "quantity": 0
    }
<p>  ]<br/>
}</p>

<p>Expected results:</p>

<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li>Status:400 Bad Request</li>
</ul>


<ul class="alternate" type="square">
	<li>Error message indicating invalid quantity value (0 not allowed)</li>
</ul>


